HEADWORD: Antiperistasis
<hw>An`ti*pe*ris"ta*sis</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`t⟦icr⟧*p⟦esl⟧*r⟦icr⟧s"t⟦adot⟧*s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'antiperi`stasis</grk>; <grk>'anti`</grk> against +
<grk>peri`stasis</grk> a standing around, fr. <grk>periista`nai</grk> to
stand around; <grk>peri`</grk> around + <grk>"ista`nai</grk> to
stand.]</ety> <def>Opposition by which the quality opposed acquires
strength; resistance or reaction roused by opposition or by the action
of an opposite principle or quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiperistatic</ent>⟦br⟧
